<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4651962>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 3. Pardosa mixta (A,E,F,H,I) and Pardosa pseudomixta sp. nov. (B–D,G). (A,B) embolic division of bulb, ventral; (C,E) embolic division of bulb, apical; (D,F) terminal apophysis; (G–I) epigyne, ventral. Arrows indicate main differences in male palp and epigyne between both species. Scale 0.1 mm, analogous figures have same scale or magnification." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4651962/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4651968>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 5. Records of Pardosa pseudomixta sp. nov. (full circles) and Pardosa mixta (full diamonds). The map also shows erroneous records of P. mixta from Uzbekistan (full squares) and presumed records of P. pseudomixta sp. nov. that were reported as P. mixta from China (open circle)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4651968/files/figure.png" .

